32template <class IndexType>
33gl::IndexRange ComputeTypedIndexRange(const IndexType *indices,
34 size_t count,
35 bool primitiveRestartEnabled,
36 GLuint primitiveRestartIndex)
37{
38 ASSERT(count > 0);
39
40 IndexType minIndex = 0;
41 IndexType maxIndex = 0;
42 size_t nonPrimitiveRestartIndices = 0;
43
44 if (primitiveRestartEnabled)
45 {
46 // Find the first non-primitive restart index to initialize the min and max values
47 size_t i = 0;
48 for (; i < count; i++)
49 {
50 if (indices[i] != primitiveRestartIndex)
51 {
52 minIndex = indices[i];
53 maxIndex = indices[i];
54 nonPrimitiveRestartIndices++;
55 break;
56 }
57 }
58
59 // Loop over the rest of the indices
60 for (; i < count; i++)
61 {
62 if (indices[i] != primitiveRestartIndex)
63 {
64 if (minIndex > indices[i])
65 {
66 minIndex = indices[i];
67 }
68 if (maxIndex < indices[i])
69 {
70 maxIndex = indices[i];
71 }
72 nonPrimitiveRestartIndices++;
73 }
74 }
75 }
76 else
77 {
78 minIndex = indices[0];
79 maxIndex = indices[0];
80 nonPrimitiveRestartIndices = count;
81
82 for (size_t i = 1; i < count; i++)
83 {
84 if (minIndex > indices[i])
85 {
86 minIndex = indices[i];
87 }
88 if (maxIndex < indices[i])
89 {
90 maxIndex = indices[i];
91 }
92 }
93 }
94
95 return gl::IndexRange(static_cast<size_t>(minIndex), static_cast<size_t>(maxIndex),
96 nonPrimitiveRestartIndices);
97}

104int VariableComponentCount(GLenum type)
105{
106 return VariableRowCount(type) * VariableColumnCount(type);
107}
108
109GLenum VariableComponentType(GLenum type)
110{
111 switch (type)
112 {
113 case GL_BOOL:
114 case GL_BOOL_VEC2:
115 case GL_BOOL_VEC3:
116 case GL_BOOL_VEC4:
117 return GL_BOOL;
118 case GL_FLOAT:
119 case GL_FLOAT_VEC2:
120 case GL_FLOAT_VEC3:
121 case GL_FLOAT_VEC4:
122 case GL_FLOAT_MAT2:
123 case GL_FLOAT_MAT3:
124 case GL_FLOAT_MAT4:
125 case GL_FLOAT_MAT2x3:
126 case GL_FLOAT_MAT3x2:
127 case GL_FLOAT_MAT2x4:
128 case GL_FLOAT_MAT4x2:
129 case GL_FLOAT_MAT3x4:
130 case GL_FLOAT_MAT4x3:
131 return GL_FLOAT;
132 case GL_INT:
133 case GL_SAMPLER_2D:
134 case GL_SAMPLER_2D_RECT_ANGLE:
135 case GL_SAMPLER_3D:
136 case GL_SAMPLER_CUBE:
137 case GL_SAMPLER_2D_ARRAY:
138 case GL_SAMPLER_EXTERNAL_OES:
139 case GL_SAMPLER_2D_MULTISAMPLE:
140 case GL_SAMPLER_2D_MULTISAMPLE_ARRAY:
141 case GL_INT_SAMPLER_2D:
142 case GL_INT_SAMPLER_3D:
143 case GL_INT_SAMPLER_CUBE:
144 case GL_INT_SAMPLER_2D_ARRAY:
145 case GL_INT_SAMPLER_2D_MULTISAMPLE:
146 case GL_INT_SAMPLER_2D_MULTISAMPLE_ARRAY:
147 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_2D:
148 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_3D:
149 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_CUBE:
150 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_2D_ARRAY:
151 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_2D_MULTISAMPLE:
152 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_2D_MULTISAMPLE_ARRAY:
153 case GL_SAMPLER_2D_SHADOW:
154 case GL_SAMPLER_CUBE_SHADOW:
155 case GL_SAMPLER_2D_ARRAY_SHADOW:
156 case GL_INT_VEC2:
157 case GL_INT_VEC3:
158 case GL_INT_VEC4:
159 case GL_IMAGE_2D:
160 case GL_INT_IMAGE_2D:
161 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_IMAGE_2D:
162 case GL_IMAGE_3D:
163 case GL_INT_IMAGE_3D:
164 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_IMAGE_3D:
165 case GL_IMAGE_2D_ARRAY:
166 case GL_INT_IMAGE_2D_ARRAY:
167 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_IMAGE_2D_ARRAY:
168 case GL_IMAGE_CUBE:
169 case GL_INT_IMAGE_CUBE:
170 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_IMAGE_CUBE:
171 case GL_IMAGE_CUBE_MAP_ARRAY:
172 case GL_INT_IMAGE_CUBE_MAP_ARRAY:
173 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_IMAGE_CUBE_MAP_ARRAY:
174 case GL_IMAGE_BUFFER:
175 case GL_INT_IMAGE_BUFFER:
176 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_IMAGE_BUFFER:
177 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_ATOMIC_COUNTER:
178 case GL_SAMPLER_VIDEO_IMAGE_WEBGL:
179 return GL_INT;
180 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT:
181 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_VEC2:
182 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_VEC3:
183 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_VEC4:
184 return GL_UNSIGNED_INT;
185 default:
186 UNREACHABLE();
187 }
188
189 return GL_NONE;
190}

192size_t VariableComponentSize(GLenum type)
193{
194 switch (type)
195 {
196 case GL_BOOL:
197 return sizeof(GLint);
198 case GL_FLOAT:
199 return sizeof(GLfloat);
200 case GL_INT:
201 return sizeof(GLint);
202 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT:
203 return sizeof(GLuint);
204 default:
205 UNREACHABLE();
206 }
207
208 return 0;
209}
210
211size_t VariableInternalSize(GLenum type)
212{
213 // Expanded to 4-element vectors
214 return VariableComponentSize(VariableComponentType(type)) * VariableRowCount(type) * 4;
215}
216
217size_t VariableExternalSize(GLenum type)
218{
219 return VariableComponentSize(VariableComponentType(type)) * VariableComponentCount(type);
220}

639bool IsOpaqueType(GLenum type)
640{
641 // ESSL 3.10 section 4.1.7 defines opaque types as: samplers, images and atomic counters.
642 return IsImageType(type) || IsSamplerType(type) || IsAtomicCounterType(type);
643}

645bool IsMatrixType(GLenum type)
646{
647 return VariableRowCount(type) > 1;
648}
649
650GLenum TransposeMatrixType(GLenum type)
651{
652 if (!IsMatrixType(type))
653 {
654 return type;
655 }
656
657 switch (type)
658 {
659 case GL_FLOAT_MAT2:
660 return GL_FLOAT_MAT2;
661 case GL_FLOAT_MAT3:
662 return GL_FLOAT_MAT3;
663 case GL_FLOAT_MAT4:
664 return GL_FLOAT_MAT4;
665 case GL_FLOAT_MAT2x3:
666 return GL_FLOAT_MAT3x2;
667 case GL_FLOAT_MAT3x2:
668 return GL_FLOAT_MAT2x3;
669 case GL_FLOAT_MAT2x4:
670 return GL_FLOAT_MAT4x2;
671 case GL_FLOAT_MAT4x2:
672 return GL_FLOAT_MAT2x4;
673 case GL_FLOAT_MAT3x4:
674 return GL_FLOAT_MAT4x3;
675 case GL_FLOAT_MAT4x3:
676 return GL_FLOAT_MAT3x4;
677 default:
678 UNREACHABLE();
679 return GL_NONE;
680 }
681}

683int MatrixRegisterCount(GLenum type, bool isRowMajorMatrix)
684{
685 ASSERT(IsMatrixType(type));
686 return isRowMajorMatrix ? VariableRowCount(type) : VariableColumnCount(type);
687}
688
689int MatrixComponentCount(GLenum type, bool isRowMajorMatrix)
690{
691 ASSERT(IsMatrixType(type));
692 return isRowMajorMatrix ? VariableColumnCount(type) : VariableRowCount(type);
693}
694
695int VariableRegisterCount(GLenum type)
696{
697 return IsMatrixType(type) ? VariableColumnCount(type) : 1;
698}

700int AllocateFirstFreeBits(unsigned int *bits, unsigned int allocationSize, unsigned int bitsSize)
701{
702 ASSERT(allocationSize <= bitsSize);
703
704 unsigned int mask = std::numeric_limits<unsigned int>::max() >>
705 (std::numeric_limits<unsigned int>::digits - allocationSize);
706
707 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < bitsSize - allocationSize + 1; i++)
708 {
709 if ((*bits & mask) == 0)
710 {
711 *bits |= mask;
712 return i;
713 }
714
715 mask <<= 1;
716 }
717
718 return -1;
719}

721IndexRange ComputeIndexRange(DrawElementsType indexType,
722 const GLvoid *indices,
723 size_t count,
724 bool primitiveRestartEnabled)
725{
726 switch (indexType)
727 {
728 case DrawElementsType::UnsignedByte:
729 return ComputeTypedIndexRange(static_cast<const GLubyte *>(indices), count,
730 primitiveRestartEnabled,
731 GetPrimitiveRestartIndex(indexType));
732 case DrawElementsType::UnsignedShort:
733 return ComputeTypedIndexRange(static_cast<const GLushort *>(indices), count,
734 primitiveRestartEnabled,
735 GetPrimitiveRestartIndex(indexType));
736 case DrawElementsType::UnsignedInt:
737 return ComputeTypedIndexRange(static_cast<const GLuint *>(indices), count,
738 primitiveRestartEnabled,
739 GetPrimitiveRestartIndex(indexType));
740 default:
741 UNREACHABLE();
742 return IndexRange();
743 }
744}

824// [OpenGL ES SL 3.00.4] Section 11 p. 120
825// Vertex Outs/Fragment Ins packing priorities
826int VariableSortOrder(GLenum type)
827{
828 switch (type)
829 {
830 // 1. Arrays of mat4 and mat4
831 // Non-square matrices of type matCxR consume the same space as a square
832 // matrix of type matN where N is the greater of C and R
833 case GL_FLOAT_MAT4:
834 case GL_FLOAT_MAT2x4:
835 case GL_FLOAT_MAT3x4:
836 case GL_FLOAT_MAT4x2:
837 case GL_FLOAT_MAT4x3:
838 return 0;
839
840 // 2. Arrays of mat2 and mat2 (since they occupy full rows)
841 case GL_FLOAT_MAT2:
842 return 1;
843
844 // 3. Arrays of vec4 and vec4
845 case GL_FLOAT_VEC4:
846 case GL_INT_VEC4:
847 case GL_BOOL_VEC4:
848 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_VEC4:
849 return 2;
850
851 // 4. Arrays of mat3 and mat3
852 case GL_FLOAT_MAT3:
853 case GL_FLOAT_MAT2x3:
854 case GL_FLOAT_MAT3x2:
855 return 3;
856
857 // 5. Arrays of vec3 and vec3
858 case GL_FLOAT_VEC3:
859 case GL_INT_VEC3:
860 case GL_BOOL_VEC3:
861 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_VEC3:
862 return 4;
863
864 // 6. Arrays of vec2 and vec2
865 case GL_FLOAT_VEC2:
866 case GL_INT_VEC2:
867 case GL_BOOL_VEC2:
868 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_VEC2:
869 return 5;
870
871 // 7. Single component types
872 case GL_FLOAT:
873 case GL_INT:
874 case GL_BOOL:
875 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT:
876 case GL_SAMPLER_2D:
877 case GL_SAMPLER_CUBE:
878 case GL_SAMPLER_EXTERNAL_OES:
879 case GL_SAMPLER_2D_RECT_ANGLE:
880 case GL_SAMPLER_2D_ARRAY:
881 case GL_SAMPLER_2D_MULTISAMPLE:
882 case GL_SAMPLER_2D_MULTISAMPLE_ARRAY:
883 case GL_SAMPLER_3D:
884 case GL_INT_SAMPLER_2D:
885 case GL_INT_SAMPLER_3D:
886 case GL_INT_SAMPLER_CUBE:
887 case GL_INT_SAMPLER_2D_ARRAY:
888 case GL_INT_SAMPLER_2D_MULTISAMPLE:
889 case GL_INT_SAMPLER_2D_MULTISAMPLE_ARRAY:
890 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_2D:
891 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_3D:
892 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_CUBE:
893 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_2D_ARRAY:
894 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_2D_MULTISAMPLE:
895 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_SAMPLER_2D_MULTISAMPLE_ARRAY:
896 case GL_SAMPLER_2D_SHADOW:
897 case GL_SAMPLER_2D_ARRAY_SHADOW:
898 case GL_SAMPLER_CUBE_SHADOW:
899 case GL_IMAGE_2D:
900 case GL_INT_IMAGE_2D:
901 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_IMAGE_2D:
902 case GL_IMAGE_3D:
903 case GL_INT_IMAGE_3D:
904 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_IMAGE_3D:
905 case GL_IMAGE_2D_ARRAY:
906 case GL_INT_IMAGE_2D_ARRAY:
907 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_IMAGE_2D_ARRAY:
908 case GL_IMAGE_CUBE:
909 case GL_INT_IMAGE_CUBE:
910 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_IMAGE_CUBE:
911 case GL_UNSIGNED_INT_ATOMIC_COUNTER:
912 case GL_SAMPLER_VIDEO_IMAGE_WEBGL:
913 return 6;
914
915 default:
916 UNREACHABLE();
917 return 0;
918 }

921std::string ParseResourceName(const std::string &name, std::vector<unsigned int> *outSubscripts)
922{
923 if (outSubscripts)
924 {
925 outSubscripts->clear();
926 }
927 // Strip any trailing array indexing operators and retrieve the subscripts.
928 size_t baseNameLength = name.length();
929 bool hasIndex = true;
930 while (hasIndex)
931 {
932 size_t open = name.find_last_of('[', baseNameLength - 1);
933 size_t close = name.find_last_of(']', baseNameLength - 1);
934 hasIndex = (open != std::string::npos) && (close == baseNameLength - 1);
935 if (hasIndex)
936 {
937 baseNameLength = open;
938 if (outSubscripts)
939 {
940 int index = atoi(name.substr(open + 1).c_str());
941 if (index >= 0)
942 {
943 outSubscripts->push_back(index);
944 }
945 else
946 {
947 outSubscripts->push_back(GL_INVALID_INDEX);
948 }
949 }
950 }
951 }
952
953 return name.substr(0, baseNameLength);
954}
955
956std::string StripLastArrayIndex(const std::string &name)
957{
958 size_t strippedNameLength = name.find_last_of('[');
959 if (strippedNameLength != std::string::npos && name.back() == ']')
960 {
961 return name.substr(0, strippedNameLength);
962 }
963 return name;
964}
965
966bool SamplerNameContainsNonZeroArrayElement(const std::string &name)
967{
968 constexpr char kZERO_ELEMENT[] = "[0]";
969
970 size_t start = 0;
971 while (true)
972 {
973 start = name.find(kZERO_ELEMENT[0], start);
974 if (start == std::string::npos)
975 {
976 break;
977 }
978 if (name.compare(start, strlen(kZERO_ELEMENT), kZERO_ELEMENT) != 0)
979 {
980 return true;
981 }
982 start++;
983 }
984 return false;
985}

987unsigned int ArraySizeProduct(const std::vector<unsigned int> &arraySizes)
988{
989 unsigned int arraySizeProduct = 1u;
990 for (unsigned int arraySize : arraySizes)
991 {
992 arraySizeProduct *= arraySize;
993 }
994 return arraySizeProduct;

996
997unsigned int ParseArrayIndex(const std::string &name, size_t *nameLengthWithoutArrayIndexOut)
998{
999 ASSERT(nameLengthWithoutArrayIndexOut != nullptr);
1000
1001 // Strip any trailing array operator and retrieve the subscript
1002 size_t open = name.find_last_of('[');
1003 if (open != std::string::npos && name.back() == ']')
1004 {
1005 bool indexIsValidDecimalNumber = true;
1006 for (size_t i = open + 1; i < name.length() - 1u; ++i)
1007 {
1008 if (!isdigit(name[i]))
1009 {
1010 indexIsValidDecimalNumber = false;
1011 break;
1012 }
1013
1014 // Leading zeroes are invalid
1015 if ((i == (open + 1)) && (name[i] == '0') && (name[i + 1] != ']'))
1016 {
1017 indexIsValidDecimalNumber = false;
1018 break;
1019 }
1020 }
1021 if (indexIsValidDecimalNumber)
1022 {
1023 errno = 0; // reset global error flag.
1024 unsigned long subscript =
1025 strtoul(name.c_str() + open + 1, /*endptr*/ nullptr, /*radix*/ 10);
1026
1027 // Check if resulting integer is out-of-range or conversion error.
1028 if (angle::base::IsValueInRangeForNumericType<uint32_t>(subscript) &&
1029 !(subscript == ULONG_MAX && errno == ERANGE) && !(errno != 0 && subscript == 0))
1030 {
1031 *nameLengthWithoutArrayIndexOut = open;
1032 return static_cast<unsigned int>(subscript);
1033 }
1034 }
1035 }
1036
1037 *nameLengthWithoutArrayIndexOut = name.length();
1038 return GL_INVALID_INDEX;
1039}

1337void writeFile(const char *path, const void *content, size_t size)
1338{
1339 FILE *file = fopen(path, "w");
1340 if (!file)
1341 {
1342 UNREACHABLE();
1343 return;
1344 }
1345
1346 fwrite(content, sizeof(char), size, file);
1347 fclose(file);
1348}
